		<hr size="1">*ahem*</P><P>In my experience, the higher your dexterity, the higher your criticals.</P><P>Or shall I say, in the past, it was glanced off of dexterity, with the higher dex, the less chance of you not crit'ing.</P><P>In todays EQ game, wizards have a...something like a 2% chance to critical cast from level 11 on.  With the maximum AA from both Luclin and PoP, which includes fury, fury mastery, and the PoP criticals, you can raise this percentage to as high as 20%.  </P><P>So, you raise the bar from 1 in 50 to 1 in 5.  Not too shabby, eh?</P><P>Now, while this might sound great and all, it comes to the whole "Does my higher than average dex, my super buffed twinked int, or my natural good looks affect my critical rates?"</P><P>NO!  N-O SPELLS NO!  NO YOU CAN NOT! NO NO NONE AT ALL!<BR>ZERO! ZILCH! NADA! GOOSE EGG! ZIP! OPPOSITE OF SOMETHING! And other such contrary statements!</P><P>However, I still like my dex to be a bit higher, because while statistically speaking dex has nothing to do with crits, I just feel luckier having a FoSoul on or something.....oh wait, thats cause having more HP is always a good thing!  Just because it buffs dex helps too though....dex does help with channeling through melee damage however.  Channeling caps off, but dex can be raised quite a bit. </P><P>Anyway, thats it for todays posting.</P><P>~ Lan</P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
