	<td>
	  <font size="2" face="Verdana">
		Subject:&nbsp;<b>RE: critical,when and how?</b></font>
		
		<a href="MB_Editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1922572&TN=critical%2Cwhen+and+how%3F&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1926128&PL=4&amp;action=REPLY"><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/btn_reply.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Reply to message"></a>
		<br>
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/Icons/icon1.gif" border="0" align="ABSCENTER" width="15" height="15">
		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 4/16/2003 8:58:13 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=114801">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Lansear Heartrender" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Lansear+Heartrender">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Lansear Heartrender" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1922572&TN=critical%2Cwhen+and+how%3F&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1926128&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Sure!  </P><P>(ahem)</P><P>I went into Najena one time for the hell of it, and ended up finding a nice camera angle by accident that I used to take a picture of myself.  Well, a lot of pictures in a bunch of different poses.</P><P>I took the screenshots and opened them with photoshop, (I have a degree in fashion design, but the curriculum made us take 4 classes on photoshop.), and I used the lasso tool to cut my character out.  I then cut and pasted the pic onto a new layer in a new picture, and made the back ground layer black.</P><P>I positioned her where I wanted, then on a new layer, I played with the text and a new font I had downloaded a few months ago, to make the Sage Lansear Heartrender.</P><P>Selecting the layer that I the text effect in, I went to the top, selected layer -> layer options, and played the effects.  (Beveled the name to give it the engraved look, inner glow to make it stand out more against the black, and a very faint and diffuse outer glow to make that dark blue back lighting effect.</P><P>For the part where it says "High Elven Aracanist, Bertoxulous server" I made a new layer and used the same font.  Rotated that layer 90 degrees, and went to Filter -> Stylize -> Wind, set it to Wind, and applied the filter, and again once.  I rotated the layer 90 degrees again to get the text facing the right way, and pressed ctrl u to bring up the hue/saturation controls, clicked where it says, "Colorize", which makes the whole layer a shade of a selected color, and played with it til I found a blue shade I liked.  I gave it a faint faint outer blue glow, and boom, a nice little ice effect was born.</P><P>Position all the layers the way you like it, save it as a PSD, press ctrl shit e to make all the layers one layer, and saved that as a jpg.</P><P>It wasn't meant to be an avater, it was meant to be a sig pic, but eh, it works.</P><P>Anyway, if you want to send me some of your screenshots through email, and a description of what you want it to look like, and if I have the time, I can put together a little avatar for ya. :-)  When I'm at 'work', heh heh heh, I'm caught up until the end of this month, so I can play with it a bit. </P><P>~ Lan </P><P>email me at nei@tampabay.rr.com</P><P>Its my cousins email account, but he forwards it to my email box which is under his account.</P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
